# I think right now that Mini has to have at least three atoms per residue,
# hence the virtual atoms.
NAME CA
IO_STRING  CA Z
TYPE LIGAND
PROPERTIES METAL
AA UNK
ROTAMERS BASIC
ATOM CA   Ca2p  Ca2p 2.00
ATOM  V1  VIRT  VIRT 0.00
ATOM  V2  VIRT  VIRT 0.00
BOND CA    V1
BOND CA    V2
CHARGE CA FORMAL +2
NET_FORMAL_CHARGE +2
NBR_ATOM CA
NBR_RADIUS 5.0
# Calcium is *not* tetrahedral--in proteins, its coord varies from ~6-8 atoms, or 2 ions
# This file was changed to match properties from the centroid params file
# Ideal bond length is 2.4 angstroms
ICOOR_INTERNAL   CA      0.000000    0.000000    0.000000  CA     V1    V2
ICOOR_INTERNAL   V1      0.000000  180.000000    2.400000  CA     V1    V2
ICOOR_INTERNAL   V2      0.000000   62.060678    2.400000  CA     V1    V2
